    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>The process of removing a mosaic or pavement from its original location to a new support and often to a new location. The process involves temporary facings, lifting or removal of the mortars, stabilization of the tessera or panels, and other issues; for various reasons, lifting is used rather than in situ stabilization treatments.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
